[Subsequent to Ep. 1153. Ep. 1164. 40-2 shows that while at Cologne (pp. 370-1), Erasmus was in hopes that a settlement with Egmondanus had been attained. It may therefore be inferred that the interview with him in Rosemondt's presence, which‘is described here (see also Ep. 1173), had then already taken place. The probable course of Erasmus’ move-ments (see p. 370) leaves room for that interview, perhaps c. 20 Oct„ before his departure to Aachen and Cologne3 but scarcely for a report of it to have reached More and for his letter inquiring about it to have then come back. This letter must therefore be later than Erasmus’ time at Cologne3 and may be placed conjec- turally in November, after his retum]
